WEBVTT

00:05.539 --> 00:09.674
♪♪

00:09.676 --> 00:11.810
Mike:
<i> Hi. My name is Mike.</i>

00:11.812 --> 00:13.612
[ Fly buzzes ]
<i> And while your house</i>
<i> is very nice,</i>

00:13.614 --> 00:15.147
<i> this isn't going to be</i>
<i> a love letter</i>

00:15.149 --> 00:17.349
<i> thanking you for</i>
<i> letting us stay here.</i>

00:17.351 --> 00:19.484
<i> We usually come to the beach</i>
<i> twice a year --</i>

00:19.486 --> 00:21.086
<i> a week</i>
<i> at the beginning of the summer</i>

00:21.088 --> 00:22.755
<i> and a week at the end.</i>

00:22.757 --> 00:25.290
<i> My wife's sister owns a place</i>
<i> right on the water.</i>

00:25.292 --> 00:26.759
<i> Her husband is a lawyer.</i>

00:28.495 --> 00:29.762
<i> My family and I rent a condo</i>

00:29.764 --> 00:31.429
<i> on the other side</i>
<i> of the freeway</i>

00:31.431 --> 00:33.766
<i> because I'm not a lawyer.</i>

00:33.768 --> 00:35.167
Guys, you've got to
pay attention.

00:35.169 --> 00:37.302
You're -- You're dropping
everything.

00:37.304 --> 00:39.838
How come Aunt Debbie
gets to stay on the beach?

00:39.840 --> 00:41.706
Because Aunt Debbie
married well.

00:41.708 --> 00:42.975
Lisa: Shh!

00:42.977 --> 00:45.243
You want a dad who represents
multi-national corporations

00:45.245 --> 00:46.645
in tort litigation?

00:46.647 --> 00:49.047
Huh? Does that seem like
a fun dad to you?

00:49.049 --> 00:52.851
♪♪

00:52.853 --> 00:54.252
♪♪

00:54.254 --> 00:56.721
[ Siren wails ]

00:56.723 --> 01:01.660
♪♪

01:01.662 --> 01:06.331
♪♪

01:06.333 --> 01:11.069
♪♪

01:11.071 --> 01:13.272
[ Coins clatter ]

01:16.210 --> 01:17.509
[ Pigeon coos ]

01:19.079 --> 01:20.745
Getting a new
credit card?

01:20.747 --> 01:22.881
Hopefully.
Mine are maxed out.

01:22.883 --> 01:25.083
Last week, I hit the limit
on my Target,

01:25.085 --> 01:28.420
and this morning, I used up my
Chevron card buying groceries.

01:28.422 --> 01:30.088
Tommy tore my cards up.

01:30.090 --> 01:32.290
Apparently, we can't afford
my obsession with shoes

01:32.292 --> 01:35.093
now that we have to
save up to get married
because we have a kid.

01:35.095 --> 01:36.628
[ Scoffs ] Yeah.

01:36.630 --> 01:38.831
Speaking of that, I'm totally
available to babysit --

01:38.833 --> 01:40.298
if the baby's
already asleep

01:40.300 --> 01:42.234
and you want to pay someone
to watch TV.

01:46.841 --> 01:49.041
Hey.
Something's wrong with my phone.

01:49.043 --> 01:51.776
Every time I call you, it goes
straight to my own voicemail.

01:51.778 --> 01:53.045
Oh, no.
That's right.

01:53.047 --> 01:54.847
After I dropped Clark
at your sister's,

01:54.849 --> 01:56.715
I stopped at the phone store
to see about reducing our bill,

01:56.717 --> 01:59.518
and after a brief, but spirited,
discussion on roaming charges,

01:59.520 --> 02:00.853
I ended up canceling
my phone

02:00.855 --> 02:03.255
and just had them forward
all my calls to yours.

02:03.257 --> 02:04.656
Oh, and I bought
a churro.

02:04.658 --> 02:06.191
I'm telling you that
'cause I feel guilty

02:06.193 --> 02:07.660
about having a dessert
when it's not the weekend.

02:07.662 --> 02:09.994
Wait, so, you're just not gonna
have a phone anymore?

02:09.996 --> 02:12.197
Well, sure I will.
We'll just share yours.

02:12.199 --> 02:14.767
[ Phone rings ]

02:16.336 --> 02:18.403
-Hello?
-Is this Nikki Gooze?

02:18.405 --> 02:19.872
Who's calling?
Is it for me?

02:19.874 --> 02:21.874
If it's a survey, don't hang up.
I actually enjoy those.

02:21.876 --> 02:23.075
Shh.

02:23.077 --> 02:25.277
This is Shyrell
from Colton Laboratories.

02:25.279 --> 02:27.680
We received your DNA sample
and your cash, but you
didn't fill in your --

02:27.682 --> 02:29.481
Yeah, um, actually,
we're not interested

02:29.483 --> 02:31.015
in a home renovation
right now,

02:31.017 --> 02:33.519
so, um, thank you so much
for calling, though.

02:35.622 --> 02:38.490
[ Laughs nervously ]

02:38.492 --> 02:42.227
Oh, also, we only get 15 texts
per month now, so...

02:42.229 --> 02:43.696
make 'em count.

02:43.698 --> 02:47.900
So, guys, I have a little
surprise for you.

02:47.902 --> 02:50.102
I was thinking, when we come
back in a few months,

02:50.104 --> 02:54.740
maybe we can get a house
on the beach, like Aunt Debbie.

02:56.510 --> 02:58.710
This place
looks awesome.

02:58.712 --> 03:00.779
[ Quietly ] Honey,
what are you doing?

03:00.781 --> 03:02.781
A place like that -- that's
gonna cost an arm and a leg.

03:02.783 --> 03:04.649
[ Quietly ] I'll figure it out.
Don't worry.

03:04.651 --> 03:07.252
You married better
than these kids think.

03:10.391 --> 03:12.925
[ Line rings ]

03:12.927 --> 03:14.727
Colton Laboratories.
This is Shyrell.

03:14.729 --> 03:17.195
Hi. This is Nikki Gooze.
You just called.

03:17.197 --> 03:18.863
Do you, um,
have my DNA results?

03:18.865 --> 03:20.733
Sweetheart, we just got
your samples today.

03:20.735 --> 03:23.001
Results can take
up to 12 weeks.

03:23.003 --> 03:25.938
I was calling you because you
didn't fill in your address.

03:25.940 --> 03:27.739
Yeah, that's because
I live with my fiancée,

03:27.741 --> 03:29.274
and he can't know
I'm doing this.

03:29.276 --> 03:31.810
Okay, so, then, we should
call you with your results.

03:31.812 --> 03:34.546
[ Phone beeps, ending the call ]
You need to quit it.

03:34.548 --> 03:35.747
Hold on a sec.

03:35.749 --> 03:37.215
[ Phone beeps ]
Hello?

03:37.217 --> 03:38.350
Uh, is Tommy there?

03:38.352 --> 03:39.618
Can you call back
in a few minutes?

03:39.620 --> 03:40.819
Okay, but I was --
[ Phone beeps ]

03:40.821 --> 03:42.887
Okay, you can't call me.
No.

03:42.889 --> 03:44.556
Yo-- you ha-- in fact,
you need to take this number
out of your system.

03:44.558 --> 03:46.424
Never call
this number again.

03:46.426 --> 03:48.226
Okay, then, we will
need an address.

03:48.228 --> 03:49.762
How about your work?

03:49.764 --> 03:52.698
Uh, work's no good.
Let me think.

03:54.168 --> 03:57.436
I swear to God, I will come over
there and punch your ass.

03:57.438 --> 03:58.903
That's right.
Punch it.

03:58.905 --> 04:01.774
I'd kick it, but my arms
are stronger than my legs.

04:01.776 --> 04:03.241
Oh, come on.
You know I'm just playing.

04:03.243 --> 04:04.977
Hey. Put a stamp on this,
would you?

04:04.979 --> 04:06.845
Vivian didn't have one,
so I told her I'd mail it

04:06.847 --> 04:08.513
for a dollar.
Doubled our money.

04:08.515 --> 04:10.182
Told you buying those
forever stamps 10 years ago

04:10.184 --> 04:11.617
was going to pay off.

04:14.120 --> 04:18.857
You know what?
Send it to 638 Carp Lane.

04:21.328 --> 04:22.995
Hiiii.

04:22.997 --> 04:24.797
If you're tired
of living in a tent,

04:24.799 --> 04:27.065
you can totally stay
at my apartment.

04:27.067 --> 04:29.267
Ah, thanks, but the tent's
not that bad.

04:29.269 --> 04:31.804
And somebody keeps dropping off
food in the morning,
so, I mean, it's --

04:31.806 --> 04:34.072
Well, I have those pillows
that memorize your head

04:34.074 --> 04:36.442
and a vegetable crisper
full of Red Bull.

04:39.946 --> 04:41.946
I'm in.
Okay.

04:41.948 --> 04:44.949
It's for you.

04:44.951 --> 04:46.351
Hello?

04:46.353 --> 04:48.153
[ Echoing ] Yes, I was calling
about the house for rent.

04:48.155 --> 04:50.489
I was wondering if it's
available the week of, uh --

04:50.491 --> 04:52.957
I'm sorry. One second.
I'm getting a bad connection.

04:52.959 --> 04:54.959
I've got an echo.
I'm going to head outside.

04:54.961 --> 04:56.561
Okay.

04:56.563 --> 04:59.297
He's gonna head outside.
He's getting a bad echo.

04:59.299 --> 05:00.833
[ Door opens ]

05:00.835 --> 05:03.368
♪♪

05:03.370 --> 05:04.769
<i> As luck would have it,</i>

05:04.771 --> 05:07.840
<i> your house was available</i>
<i> the week we needed it.</i>

05:07.842 --> 05:11.176
<i> I just had to figure out</i>
<i> a way to pay for it,</i>

05:11.178 --> 05:13.045
<i> which meant pulling</i>
<i> double shifts at work</i>

05:13.047 --> 05:14.579
<i> for the next two months.</i>

05:14.581 --> 05:16.581
<i> And the plan was going</i>
<i> pretty smooth until one night,</i>

05:16.583 --> 05:19.451
<i> during the tail end of a double</i>
<i> shift, I was really tired,</i>

05:19.453 --> 05:21.520
<i> and I wasn't paying attention</i>
<i> to where I was walking...</i>

05:21.522 --> 05:22.454
[ Truck beeping ]

05:22.456 --> 05:24.556
Whoa!
[ Glass shatters ]

05:25.992 --> 05:28.593
<i> ...which led to</i>
<i> a bit of an accident.</i>

05:28.595 --> 05:32.665
[ Bone crunches ]
[ Screams, cries ]

05:32.667 --> 05:35.200
<i> Turns out, my wife was wrong</i>
<i> about your house.</i>

05:35.202 --> 05:37.736
[ Fly buzzes ]
<i> It didn't cost me</i>
<i> an arm and a leg.</i>

05:40.474 --> 05:41.940
<i> Just a leg.</i>

05:47.514 --> 05:49.448
<i> You learn a lot of things</i>
<i> when you lose a limb.</i>

05:49.450 --> 05:51.716
<i> For one, you learn you don't</i>
<i> just buy a prosthetic leg</i>

05:51.718 --> 05:53.786
<i> off the rack.</i>
<i> They have to fit you for it,</i>

05:53.788 --> 05:55.788
<i> and it takes a few months</i>
<i> to get made.</i>

05:55.790 --> 06:02.795
♪♪

06:02.797 --> 06:05.864
<i> You also learn that children</i>
<i> get pretty freaked out</i>

06:05.866 --> 06:07.599
<i> by a missing limb...</i>

06:07.601 --> 06:11.670
<i> no matter how hard your wife</i>
<i> tries to make it fun for them.</i>

06:11.672 --> 06:12.937
All right, kids.

06:12.939 --> 06:16.642
Who wants to meet Daddy's
new friend, Mr. Whiskers?

06:19.279 --> 06:20.813
[ Quietly ] You go.

06:20.815 --> 06:22.014
Go.

06:22.016 --> 06:30.422
♪♪

06:30.424 --> 06:33.558
<i> And while they prescribe</i>
<i> anti-bacterial soap</i>

06:33.560 --> 06:36.829
<i> to help protect you</i>
<i> from infection...</i>

06:36.831 --> 06:38.497
<i> you learn they don't</i>
<i> prescribe anything</i>

06:38.499 --> 06:39.898
<i> to protect your feelings.</i>

06:39.900 --> 06:41.500
[ Gags ]

06:41.502 --> 06:43.435
I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

06:43.437 --> 06:46.905
It's the first time that
I've seen it naked.

06:46.907 --> 06:48.106
It's not that bad.

06:48.108 --> 06:49.408
[ Gags ]

06:52.913 --> 06:54.713
<i> The next thing you learn</i>
<i> is that you don't</i>

06:54.715 --> 06:56.048
<i> get to pick your home nurse.</i>

06:56.050 --> 06:58.050
That's good.
That's good. Okay.

06:58.052 --> 06:59.051
Oh!

06:59.053 --> 07:02.787
Relax. Relax.
Let me steer.

07:02.789 --> 07:04.923
I am the captain now.

07:04.925 --> 07:07.459
[ Laughs ]

07:07.461 --> 07:09.594
That was from a movie
with Tommy Hanks.

07:09.596 --> 07:11.329
"I am the captain now."

07:11.331 --> 07:12.531
You see,
there was a gentleman

07:12.533 --> 07:14.599
who sounded like me
who was a pirate,

07:14.601 --> 07:17.135
and when he took charge
of Tommy Hanks' boat,

07:17.137 --> 07:18.603
he looked at him
and he said --

07:18.605 --> 07:20.805
"I am the captain now."
Yeah. I saw the movie.

07:20.807 --> 07:22.474
Yeah, we saw it.

07:22.476 --> 07:26.611
<i> Then, you learn you can't even</i>
<i> sleep in your own bed anymore.</i>

07:26.613 --> 07:28.480
[ Gasps ]
Oh, Mike!

07:28.482 --> 07:30.815
Oh, it touched
me again.

07:30.817 --> 07:32.217
The stump --
it poked through

07:32.219 --> 07:33.818
the pillow barrier,
and it touched me.

07:33.820 --> 07:35.820
What the hell do you
want me to do?!

07:35.822 --> 07:37.489
I thought you were gonna
wear the kitty-cat cozy
that I made for you.

07:37.491 --> 07:40.292
When I wear Mr. Whiskers,
my stump gets hot, it sweats,

07:40.294 --> 07:42.294
and you complain
it smells like old mayonnaise.

07:42.296 --> 07:44.830
Pick your poison, Lisa.
Pick your poison!

07:46.433 --> 07:47.700
Mayonnaise.

07:49.770 --> 07:51.703
<i> But the worst thing</i>
<i> was the boredom.</i>

07:51.705 --> 07:55.107
<i> The days turned into weeks,</i>
<i> the weeks turned into months,</i>

07:55.109 --> 07:59.778
<i> and before you know it,</i>
<i> we lose all track of time.</i>

07:59.780 --> 08:01.180
Lisa!

08:04.318 --> 08:06.785
Why are you yelling?

08:06.787 --> 08:08.520
Why aren't we
at the beach?

08:08.522 --> 08:10.255
We were supposed to start using
the house three days ago.

08:10.257 --> 08:12.725
I just figured
with everything going on...

08:12.727 --> 08:14.726
Mike, I mean, you haven't
left the house all summer.

08:14.728 --> 08:18.130
I lost 9 inches of my leg
for a week in that house, Lisa!

08:18.132 --> 08:21.199
Every day we don't use it
is 1.3 inches of flesh

08:21.201 --> 08:22.334
I lost for nothing.

08:22.336 --> 08:25.604
I lost an ankle
for nothing!

08:25.606 --> 08:27.339
Kids, pack your shit!

08:27.341 --> 08:28.640
We're going to the beach!

08:29.744 --> 08:33.011
Good morning. Oh, wonderful.
You're off the chair.

08:33.013 --> 08:35.480
I'll take this opportunity
to Febreze the cushions.

08:35.482 --> 08:36.749
We're going to the beach!

08:36.751 --> 08:39.084
Splendid. The salt water
is actually good

08:39.086 --> 08:40.352
for healing wounds.

08:40.354 --> 08:42.955
You hear that, Lisa?
Maybe my leg will grow back!

08:42.957 --> 08:45.958
Perhaps it will!

08:45.960 --> 08:47.692
That will never happen.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.093
But they told us
in nursing school

08:49.095 --> 08:50.895
that optimism has been
clinically proven

08:50.897 --> 08:54.400
to faster get a patient
back on their feet -- foot.

08:57.104 --> 08:58.703
<i> Every second I wasn't</i>

08:58.705 --> 09:00.305
<i> in your rental house,</i>
<i> I was losing money.</i>

09:00.307 --> 09:01.907
<i> So we packed up the wagon</i>
<i> and hauled ass to the beach.</i>

09:01.909 --> 09:04.843
[ Mail man singing
indistinctly ]

09:04.845 --> 09:08.480
♪♪

09:11.718 --> 09:15.554
♪♪

09:18.725 --> 09:20.225
Vivian:
[ Quietly ] Yes!

09:24.131 --> 09:26.131
Vivian?

09:26.133 --> 09:28.934
Bodhi: Vivian?

09:28.936 --> 09:30.335
Yeah?

09:30.337 --> 09:32.071
Look what I found
in the bathroom.

09:32.073 --> 09:33.538
[ Surprised ]
What is that?!

09:33.540 --> 09:35.941
It's a camera
in a tissue box.

09:52.359 --> 09:54.693
Where did you get
this tissue box?

09:54.695 --> 10:00.231
Um, I -- I think that I got it
at the drug store over on Maple.

10:00.233 --> 10:01.767
Some creep at
the drug store

10:01.769 --> 10:03.902
must be putting cameras
in tissue boxes

10:03.904 --> 10:06.305
so he can watch women shower
from his computer.

10:06.307 --> 10:07.773
[ Exhales deeply ] What?
Yeah.

10:07.775 --> 10:09.641
We should go down
to that drug store

10:09.643 --> 10:12.577
and buy all the tissue boxes so
that no other women have to --

10:12.579 --> 10:13.979
do I smell
Hot Pockets?

10:13.981 --> 10:15.180
Oh. Yeah.

10:15.182 --> 10:17.248
Bacon and cheddar --
your favorite. [ Chuckles ]

10:17.250 --> 10:19.651
I'm cooking them in the oven
because you said the microwave

10:19.653 --> 10:21.252
doesn't crust them up
like you like.

10:21.254 --> 10:22.587
And -- and if that
doesn't work,

10:22.589 --> 10:24.389
I can start experimenting
with basting.

10:24.391 --> 10:26.792
Wow.
Vivian, you're the best.

10:26.794 --> 10:27.793
Oh.

10:27.795 --> 10:29.260
I don't know how I'm ever
gonna repay you

10:29.262 --> 10:31.062
for letting me stay here.

10:31.064 --> 10:33.999
Well, I'm sure we'll
think of something.

10:34.001 --> 10:36.467
In the meantime, why don't you
give me this camera,

10:36.469 --> 10:39.404
and I'm gonna make
a formal complaint.

10:39.406 --> 10:41.606
You know what?
I've got a better idea.

10:41.608 --> 10:43.008
I'm going to put this back
in the bathroom,

10:43.010 --> 10:46.011
stand right in front of it,
and jerk off. Yeah.

10:46.013 --> 10:47.612
Let's give that
drug-store creep

10:47.614 --> 10:49.481
a whole lot more
than he bargained for.

10:49.483 --> 10:51.984
[ Laughs ]

10:52.553 --> 10:56.087
[ Door closes ]

10:56.089 --> 10:57.356
[ Sighs ]

10:58.225 --> 11:00.091
Oh, yeah.

11:00.093 --> 11:04.095
♪♪

11:04.097 --> 11:06.565
Hey. Hey!
There's lotion under the sink!

11:11.172 --> 11:13.104
<i> Anyway, my point</i>
<i> in writing all of this</i>

11:13.106 --> 11:14.973
<i> is that you should think about</i>
<i> lowering your rental price,</i>

11:14.975 --> 11:17.776
<i> so an average family of four</i>
<i> can go on a nice vacation</i>

11:17.778 --> 11:19.044
<i> without losing a limb.</i>

11:19.046 --> 11:21.913
<i> That's right.</i>
<i> I blame you.</i>

11:21.915 --> 11:22.915
<i> Mike.</i>

11:25.719 --> 11:28.720
[ Laughing ]

11:28.722 --> 11:31.122
That's not funny!

11:31.124 --> 11:34.059
Oh, come on.
They're just having fun.

11:34.061 --> 11:36.127
Look at the little seashells
they used as toenails.

11:36.129 --> 11:37.596
Tell me that doesn't
make you smile.

11:37.598 --> 11:39.198
[ Laughing ]

11:39.200 --> 11:40.399
You think this is funny?!

11:40.401 --> 11:41.733
I'm crippled!

11:41.735 --> 11:43.068
Why don't you go
tell your parents

11:43.070 --> 11:44.403
you made fun of a cripple,
you little pricks?!

11:44.405 --> 11:46.205
Go on! Get!

11:46.207 --> 11:48.473
♪♪

11:48.475 --> 11:50.542
[ Grunts ]

11:50.544 --> 11:54.345
Hot. Hot. Hot.
Hot. Hot. Hot. Hot.

11:54.347 --> 11:57.016
Hot! Hot! Hot!
Maybe the kids can all sleep
over at my place tonight.

11:57.018 --> 12:01.220
Mike seems like he could use
a break...or a blowjob.

12:01.222 --> 12:02.655
Thanks.

12:07.160 --> 12:08.427
Mike?

12:10.564 --> 12:13.632
♪♪

12:13.634 --> 12:15.567
Mike?!
Where are you going?!

12:15.569 --> 12:17.302
I'm going home.
The sand is too hot.

12:17.304 --> 12:20.839
People keep staring at me.
This was a stupid idea.

12:20.841 --> 12:22.774
Wait, you're just gonna
leave us here?

12:22.776 --> 12:24.910
You're acting insane!

12:24.912 --> 12:28.247
Insane?! I'm acting like a guy
who lost his leg, Lisa!

12:28.249 --> 12:34.420
Trust me. You have no idea
what it's like to be in my shoe!

12:36.924 --> 12:38.189
The second we get back
to the house,

12:38.191 --> 12:40.125
I'm checking these things
for cameras.

12:40.127 --> 12:41.460
Good idea.

12:41.462 --> 12:43.128
You know,
we should probably

12:43.130 --> 12:45.063
also check each other
for cameras.

12:45.065 --> 12:47.398
You know, kind of like how,
after you go hiking,

12:47.400 --> 12:48.667
you check for ticks.

12:51.338 --> 12:53.072
Eddie?!

12:53.074 --> 12:55.073
I got to go.

12:55.075 --> 12:57.342
Bodhi: Buddy.
Where have you been?

12:57.344 --> 12:59.945
If you've been hiding,
you don't have to.

12:59.947 --> 13:03.081
I'm not pissed that you
burned down my van/home.

13:03.083 --> 13:04.683
I know it was
an accident.

13:04.685 --> 13:06.752
I'm not gonna
kick your ass.

13:06.754 --> 13:08.820
Okay, uh, first of all,
I'm pretty sure

13:08.822 --> 13:10.221
I could beat the shit
out of you,

13:10.223 --> 13:12.223
but let's put a pin in that
for the moment.

13:12.225 --> 13:14.693
I was hoping the next time I saw
you, I would be finished.

13:14.695 --> 13:16.128
Finished with what?

13:19.566 --> 13:22.301
I got it from
a yard sale of sorts.

13:22.303 --> 13:24.303
Basically, I saw it
sitting in someone's yard

13:24.305 --> 13:25.938
and I asked if it
was for sale.

13:30.043 --> 13:33.044
I tried to replace all the stuff
that was inside.

13:33.046 --> 13:35.246
Here's a new
action figure.

13:35.248 --> 13:36.715
Handsome Man.

13:36.717 --> 13:38.117
I made his gi
flame-retardant,

13:38.119 --> 13:42.921
so, God forbid, he doesn't die
the same way twice.

13:42.923 --> 13:44.856
[ Voice breaking ]
I don't know what to say.

13:44.858 --> 13:47.126
I can't believe
you did this.

13:47.128 --> 13:48.527
Well, I had to, man.

13:48.529 --> 13:50.195
My substandard
joint extinguishment

13:50.197 --> 13:51.863
destroyed your van/home.

13:51.865 --> 13:53.665
I would never
blame you for that!

13:53.667 --> 13:57.402
Well, I know.
That's why I had to do it.

13:57.404 --> 13:59.905
[ Both crying ]

14:01.608 --> 14:03.475
Were you the one
who was leaving the food

14:03.477 --> 14:05.677
outside my tent
on the beach?

14:05.679 --> 14:08.413
I didn't want you
to be hungry.

14:08.415 --> 14:09.881
Thanks. [ Sniffs ]

14:09.883 --> 14:12.083
But for the record,

14:12.085 --> 14:15.154
I like my peanut butter smooth,
not crunchy.

14:15.156 --> 14:17.489
I wish I would have
known that!

14:17.491 --> 14:20.425
[ Sobbing ]

14:20.427 --> 14:24.629
♪♪

14:24.765 --> 14:31.804
♪♪

14:34.842 --> 14:36.241
God damn it!

14:36.243 --> 14:39.178
I left my credit card
at the beach.

14:39.180 --> 14:40.512
Let's go.

14:46.119 --> 14:51.190
Keep it running?
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

14:51.192 --> 14:53.826
[ Grunting ]

14:56.930 --> 14:58.329
Man: [ Grunts ]

14:58.331 --> 15:00.599
Lisa!

15:00.601 --> 15:03.668
Shit. Mike!
This is nothing!

15:03.670 --> 15:07.138
I had too many beers, and he let
me cry on his shoulder.

15:07.140 --> 15:09.875
And then, we just --
we smoked a little hash,

15:09.877 --> 15:12.811
and we watched a little porn
on his phone,

15:12.813 --> 15:14.913
and then,
this just happened!

15:16.950 --> 15:20.952
Mike! Mike!
Mike, wait!

15:20.954 --> 15:25.023
Oh, my God. What did I do?
What did I do?

15:25.025 --> 15:28.093
This is not your fault.
I am to blame.

15:28.095 --> 15:30.896
Sometimes, I can't control
my desire to comfort.

15:30.898 --> 15:32.764
No, you need to leave.

15:32.766 --> 15:34.099
Are you sure?

15:34.101 --> 15:35.834
Because I believe
the orgasm count

15:35.836 --> 15:38.303
is Lisa: 1, Kwame: 0.

15:38.305 --> 15:40.105
Don't we think should
even things out --

15:40.107 --> 15:41.306
No.

15:41.308 --> 15:42.608
-Huh?
-No.

15:46.379 --> 15:47.913
♪♪

15:47.915 --> 15:49.781
[ Crying, sniffling ]

15:49.783 --> 15:54.720
♪♪

15:54.722 --> 15:59.791
♪♪

15:59.793 --> 16:03.762
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

16:05.732 --> 16:09.635
♪♪

16:11.538 --> 16:16.008
♪♪

16:24.818 --> 16:28.821
[ Ominous music plays ]

16:30.690 --> 16:36.361
♪♪

16:36.363 --> 16:39.030
[ Grunts ]

16:39.032 --> 16:40.832
[ Door creaks open ]

16:40.834 --> 16:44.536
♪♪

16:47.575 --> 16:48.974
[ Breathes heavily ]

16:53.046 --> 16:55.380
[ "Walk a Mile in My Shoes"
plays ]

16:55.382 --> 16:58.250
<i> Perspective is</i>
<i> an interesting thing.</i>

16:58.252 --> 17:00.919
<i> And sometimes, to truly</i>
<i> understand why someone does</i>

17:00.921 --> 17:02.988
<i> the things they do,</i>
<i> you need to imagine</i>

17:02.990 --> 17:05.857
<i> what would have happened if the</i>
<i> shoe wasn't on the other foot.</i>

17:05.859 --> 17:10.128
♪♪

17:10.130 --> 17:14.600
♪ If I could be you,
and you could be me ♪

17:14.602 --> 17:16.067
♪ Just for one hour... ♪

17:16.069 --> 17:18.736
<i> Instead of being wrapped up</i>
<i> in your own problems,</i>

17:18.738 --> 17:20.405
<i> you need to consider</i>
<i> what other people</i>

17:20.407 --> 17:21.673
<i> might be going through...</i>

17:21.675 --> 17:25.477
♪ ...get inside
each other's mind ♪

17:25.479 --> 17:27.345
<i> ...the things they're</i>
<i> having to deal with...</i>

17:27.347 --> 17:29.281
♪ If you could see you ♪
Sorry.

17:29.283 --> 17:31.883
♪ Through my eyes... ♪
<i> ...and how you might not be</i>
<i> the only person</i>

17:31.885 --> 17:33.685
<i> trying to cope with</i>
<i> a shitty situation.</i>

17:33.687 --> 17:35.553
♪♪

17:35.555 --> 17:38.156
♪ I believe you'd be
surprised to see ♪

17:38.158 --> 17:40.626
Ooh! Lisa! No,
your stump touched me again!

17:40.628 --> 17:42.628
You're gonna have to pick
your poison, Mike!

17:42.630 --> 17:44.362
♪ Walk a mile in my shoes ♪
Pants?

17:44.364 --> 17:47.299
I lost 9 inches of my leg
for that beach house, Mike.

17:47.301 --> 17:49.701
♪ Walk a mile in my shoes ♪

17:49.703 --> 17:51.637
Pack your shit!
We're going to the beach!

17:51.639 --> 17:54.973
♪ Before you abuse,
criticize, and accuse ♪

17:54.975 --> 17:56.708
♪ Walk a mile in my shoes ♪
Hey, that's not funny.

17:56.710 --> 17:59.044
I'm acting like a woman
who lost her leg, Mike!

17:59.046 --> 18:02.714
♪ Now your whole world ♪
You have no idea
what it's like to be in my shoe!

18:02.716 --> 18:04.382
♪ You see around you... ♪

18:04.384 --> 18:07.653
<i> And when we're hurting,</i>
<i> stressed, and vulnerable,</i>

18:07.655 --> 18:09.921
<i> we're all capable</i>
<i> of making decisions</i>

18:09.923 --> 18:11.056
<i> that we might later regret.</i>

18:11.058 --> 18:12.991
♪ Says you're gonna reap ♪

18:12.993 --> 18:14.259
♪ Just what you sow ♪
Mike?

18:14.261 --> 18:15.593
Oh, shit.
No, no, no, no.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.463
This isn't
what it looks like.

18:17.465 --> 18:22.600
♪ So unless you've lived a life
of total perfection ♪

18:22.602 --> 18:24.470
<i> So, I'm sure you have</i>
<i> a good reason</i>

18:24.472 --> 18:25.937
<i> why you charge</i>
<i> the rent you charge</i>

18:25.939 --> 18:27.539
<i> for your beach house.</i>

18:27.541 --> 18:30.942
<i> And if I was in your situation,</i>
<i> I might do the same.</i>

18:30.944 --> 18:36.815
<i> I apologize for what I wrote</i>
<i> earlier -- your pal, Mike.</i>

18:36.817 --> 18:38.150
Mike.

18:38.152 --> 18:40.152
Oh, my God.
I'm so sorry.

18:40.154 --> 18:41.687
I understand.

18:41.689 --> 18:43.555
-You do?
-Yes.

18:46.226 --> 18:49.294
I've been so focused on
what I was going through,

18:49.296 --> 18:52.164
I didn't realize what
you were going through.

18:52.166 --> 18:56.568
I know this hasn't been
easy on you, either.

18:56.570 --> 18:59.037
I forgive you.

18:59.039 --> 19:02.574
Oh. I -- I should
brush my teeth first.

19:02.576 --> 19:04.309
I think I blew Kwame.

19:04.311 --> 19:05.577
I appreciate that.

19:05.579 --> 19:06.778
♪♪

19:06.780 --> 19:07.913
[ Children laughing ]

19:07.915 --> 19:09.848
♪ Walk a mile in my shoe ♪

19:09.850 --> 19:11.983
Hey! [ Laughs ]

19:11.985 --> 19:16.388
♪ Walk a mile in my sho-o-oe ♪

19:16.390 --> 19:20.325
♪ Before you abuse,
criticize, and accuse ♪

19:20.327 --> 19:25.397
♪ Walk a mile in my shoe ♪

19:25.399 --> 19:29.267
♪ Now, your whole world
you see around you ♪

19:29.269 --> 19:33.872
♪ Is just a reflection ♪

19:33.874 --> 19:35.541
♪ And the law of karma ♪

19:35.543 --> 19:42.680
♪ Says you're gonna reap
just what you sow ♪

19:42.682 --> 19:45.417
♪ So, unless you've
lived a life ♪
Hey!

19:45.419 --> 19:48.554
♪ Of total perfection ♪

19:48.556 --> 19:50.356
She's stealing
my mail!

19:50.358 --> 19:52.490
♪ You'd better be careful ♪

19:52.492 --> 19:58.630
♪ Of every stone
that you should throw ♪

19:58.632 --> 20:00.566
♪ And yet
we spend the day ♪

20:00.568 --> 20:06.838
♪ Throwing stones
at one another ♪

20:06.840 --> 20:15.380
♪ 'Cause I don't think or wear
my hair the same way you do ♪

20:15.382 --> 20:19.317
♪ Yeah, well,
I may be common people ♪

20:19.319 --> 20:21.487
♪ But I'm still
your sister ♪

20:23.591 --> 20:27.726
♪ When you strike out
and try to hurt me ♪

20:27.728 --> 20:31.196
♪ It's hurting you ♪

20:31.198 --> 20:35.333
♪ Walk a mile
in my shoes ♪

20:35.335 --> 20:39.938
♪ Walk a mile in my shoes ♪

20:39.940 --> 20:43.875
♪ Before you abuse,
criticize, and accuse ♪

20:43.877 --> 20:47.745
♪ Walk a mile in my shoes ♪

20:47.747 --> 20:49.347
[ Answering machine beeps ]
Woman:
<i> Hey, Clem. It's me.</i>

20:49.349 --> 20:50.949
<i> We're renting a beach house</i>
<i> this weekend,</i>

20:50.951 --> 20:52.618
<i> and we'd love to see you.</i>

20:52.620 --> 20:55.087
<i> Maybe you can bring that girl</i>
<i> we've heard about.</i>

20:55.089 --> 21:00.092
